ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 2
 presents the projected density of states (PDOS) of the GQD/Pt(II) complex nanocomposite. The HOMO and LUMO energy levels of the nanocomposite are influenced by the Pt(II) complex states, while the GQD states reside deep within the valence band (VB) and conduction band (CB). The deep energy states of GQDs facilitate the transfer of photo-generated charges to the Pt(II) complex, effectively separating electron-hole pairs (Fig. 3
) and minimizing recombination, which can cause energy loss. This reduced recombination leads to higher photocatalytic efficiency. Furthermore, GQDs, confined within the bands, bridge the energy gap between the HOMO and LUMO of the photocatalyst, creating a favorable environment for electron transitions and enhancing light absorption properties. This bridging expands the photocatalytic activity across various light spectra.
